Royal Philips to Name Jeroen van der Veer as Chairman

-- B y   M a u d   v a n   G a a l
-- 
2011-02-17T17:51:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-17/royal-philips-to-name-jeroen-van-der-veer-as-chairman-update1-.html
Royal Philips Electronics NV, the
world’s biggest lighting company, said Jeroen van der Veer will
become chairman of its supervisory board on March 31, succeeding
Jan-Michiel Hessels, who is retiring.  Van der Veer has been on the supervisory board since 2009,
when he stepped down as Chief Executive Officer of  Royal Dutch
Shell Plc . He also holds board positions at ING Groep NV, the
biggest Dutch financial services company, and Unilever Plc.,
Amsterdam-based Philips said in a statement today  “We are pleased to welcome Jeroen van der Veer in his new
role as Chairman of the Supervisory Board,” said Chief
Executive Officer Gerard Kleisterlee, who is also stepping down
in March. “His extensive experience will be invaluable in
helping Philips’ board of management achieve the company’s
ambitions for growth”  Hessels headed the supervisory board for the last three
years, after joining it in 1999.  Kleisterlee will be appointed as a non-executive director
of Vodafone Group Plc on April 1 before becoming chairman at the
annual meeting in July.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Maud van Gaal at 
 mvangaal@bloomberg.net  